text:
Keith has been super professional from the beginning and just a real true American that gets the job done right.

He will do the job as he would his own home. He came to do the work when the temperature and weather conditions were just right.

He and his team transformed a gravel driveway from a disaster to a total relief.

I really wouldn't look anywhere else as they pride themselves on the work and did a fantastic job all around.

If you want the right care and trust go with PM Paving they will get it done right!

A lot of companies the ownership will not be on site but, Keith and his son were right there getting it done. I even heard Keith say things like "add more material here, I want it done right, we shouldn't have to come back out here do it right once, etc. They even helped out to dismantle an entire garage tent and it's electrical including relocating all items inside.

GO WITH PM PAVING they do most of the schools, Taco Casa's, etc in town and I'm just a homeowner and Keith definitely has care to do the job right.

text:
I do not recommend this company. They're not professionals, they're liars. He will come quickly for the check, but he will never do what he should  to do.  When you start pointing out shortcomings, he will first promise to do it, but he will do not it. And when you continue to insist, the answer will be aggressive. 1. We ordered a calvert without asphalt coating.  Look at the photos, what they promised and what we got. 2. We ordered to bring sand to raise the level of the site. We didn't get a single loadful of sand. They just raked the mounds from the higher areas to the lower areas. At the same time, the entire site was threatened with flooding. He also blocked stormwater way. Rainwater has nowhere to go, the site was flooded. In his opinion, we should pay for the repair of his broken grader. And also we should pay for the work of 8 people, although only 1 worked.
I've never seen such a blatant and blatant deception before.
